    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.5.65-66"/>
                <note type="curatorial">65</note>
                <note type="curatorial">
                    Piper Collection 
                    25
                </note>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    276 Linwood 
                    Buffalo NcYc 
                </ab> 
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    BUFFALO DEC 16 130 PM 1924 N.Y.
                </ab> 
                
                <ab type="stamp">
                    UNITEDSTATESPOSTAGE JEFFERSON 2CENTS2
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    Miss Mildred Piper 
                    <del>809 North Hastings</del>
                    Hastings
                    Nebraska
                </ab> 
            </div1>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.5.65-66"/>
                <note type="curatorial">66</note>
                
                <opener>
                    
                    <dateline>
                        276 Linwood Ave 
                        Buffalo N.Y.
                        Nov. 16-1924
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>My Dear little girl;</salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>Such pleasant thots fill me this morning because they surround you. The pleasant times and the happy days you spent with me I so long to have repeated. You know</p> 
                <p>my dear you are my ideal and when ever I want to compare to someone worth while it is, "Just like Miss Piper." My dear this is carrying to you good cheer for christmas and best wishes for the New Years</p> <closer><salute>with love</salute> <signed>Alice McNeihardt</signed></closer>
                
            </div1>
            
        </body>
        
